const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'AMD$130K-207K', annual: 'AMD$1.56M-2.48M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'AMD$178K-276K', annual: 'AMD$2.14M-3.31M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'AMD$240K-370K', annual: 'AMD$2.88M-4.44M' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'AMD$10K-25K/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'AMD$40K-100K/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Armenia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Armenia. Ancient culture, affordable living, diaspora welcome, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Armenia"
  subheadline="Armenia offers ancient Christian heritage, stunning mountain landscapes, welcoming diaspora policies, affordable living, and improving healthcare—a hidden gem for budget-conscious retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/armenia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Armenia</h2>
  <p>
    Armenia offers ancient Christian heritage (first Christian nation), stunning Caucasus mountains, welcoming diaspora policies, very affordable living, and improving infrastructure. For Armenian diaspora or adventurous retirees seeking value and culture, Armenia delivers unique experience.
  </p>

  <p>
    Yerevan is the capital with best healthcare, cafes, and cultural life. Lake Sevan offers mountain retreat. Dilijan is "Armenia's Switzerland." Gyumri provides second-city character. Most retirees choose Yerevan for services; others explore regions for lower costs.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; good private options in Yerevan</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Armenian; Russian; English growing</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> AMD$400K-800K/month (~$1,000-2,000 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; hot summers; cold winters</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Ancient; hospitable; diaspora-friendly</li>
      <li><strong>Visa:</strong> Many nationalities visa-free or e-visa</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Armenia Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Armenia healthcare is improving—private hospitals in Yerevan offer good quality. Astghik Medical Center, Nairi Medical Center, and Nork-Marash Medical Center are leading facilities. Quality has improved with diaspora investment. Complex cases may need Tbilisi, Istanbul, or Europe.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is limited. Private care is affordable and increasingly modern. Yerevan has best options; regional healthcare is basic. International insurance with evacuation coverage recommended for comprehensive security.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Regional Backup</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Yerevan healthcare handles most conditions well. Complex cases may need Tbilisi (3 hours) or Istanbul. European hospitals accessible by flight. Ensure insurance includes regional evacuation. Healthcare improving but not yet comprehensive for all specialties.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Armenia has accessible visa policies:
  </p>

  <h3>Visa-Free/E-Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Many nationalities visa-free or simple e-visa. US, EU citizens often 180 days visa-free in 1-year period.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For long-term residence. Various categories including retiree, investor, employment. Straightforward process.
  </p>

  <h3>Ethnic Armenian (Repatriation)</h3>
  <p>
    Special provisions for ethnic Armenians. Faster path to residence and citizenship. Diaspora welcomed.
  </p>

  <h3>Special Residence</h3>
  <p>
    10-year residence for qualified individuals including pensioners with income.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Armenia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> No insurance required for short stays</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance may be required</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Regional:</strong> Include Turkey/Georgia/Europe access</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Armenia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance recommended despite affordable local care. Provides evacuation to regional centers for complex conditions. High-deductible plans work well with affordable Yerevan care. Local options have age limits and coverage restrictions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Armenia, evacuation coverage important:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Armenia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Worldwide coverage, strong network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Works well with affordable local care</li>
    <li><strong>Regional access:</strong> Istanbul, Tbilisi backup</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage options for Armenia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Armenia (AMD ~400 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Self-pay routine:</strong> Doctor visits ~$25-60</li>
    <li><strong>Yerevan base:</strong> Best healthcare access</li>
    <li><strong>Regional network:</strong> Turkey/Georgia for complex needs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Armenian-American Repatriate, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month pension. Ethnic Armenian return. Yerevan.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with $2,500 deductible. Self-pay routine care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~AMD$155,000/month (~$390). Ancestral homeland; affordable living.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: French Explorer, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,000/month pension. Residence permit. Dilijan.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with Europe coverage. Mountain lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~AMD$200,000/month (~$500). European backup; nature living.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Russian Speaker, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,800/month income. Visa-free rotation. Yerevan center.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with high deductible.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~AMD$145,000/month (~$360). Language ease; budget lifestyle.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Armenia safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—low crime rates. Avoid border areas with Azerbaijan (ongoing tensions). Yerevan is safe for walking. Political protests occasionally occur. Overall peaceful destination for expats. Regional geopolitics are consideration.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Armenian or Russian?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful—English growing but limited outside Yerevan expat circles. Russian widely spoken (Soviet legacy). Armenian useful for deeper integration. Healthcare providers often speak Russian or English. Language barrier exists outside capital.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How cold are winters?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Cold—Yerevan winters average below freezing. Snow is common. Mountain areas colder. Summers are hot (35°C+). Four distinct seasons. Infrastructure handles cold well. Not tropical retirement; continental climate reality.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about regional tensions?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Armenia-Azerbaijan conflict is ongoing concern. Border areas should be avoided. Yerevan and tourist regions are safe. Monitor situation before travel. Geopolitical reality is factor but doesn't affect daily life in most areas.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Armenia coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Armenia authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
